{"key":"post-12328580","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>12328580</id>\n<content>Thanks for the tip, but since one mists from the very first day cakes are added, the proper frequency of misting keeps the perlite hydrated and it doesn't dry out.&amp;nbsp; I've gone months without re-soaking the perlite and had upper 90% humidity the whole time.&amp;nbsp; The key is misting.&amp;nbsp; Fresh air dries out the substrate &lt;i&gt;and&lt;/i&gt; the perlite, both of which are then replenished by frequent misting.&amp;nbsp; This ebb and flow of substrate moisture content is a major pinning trigger.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>12336717</next>\n<prev>12328476</prev>\n<first>12327900</first>\n<last>12337403</last>\n<when>1270403009</when>\n<utime>04/04/10 08:43 PM</utime>\n</post>"}